<p>The earliest recorded representations of dancing figures within Iran were found in prehistoric sites such as Tepe Sialk and Tepe MÅ«sÄ«Än.<sup id="cite_ref-473" class="reference"><a href="Persia#cite_note-473">&#91;471&#93;</a></sup> The oldest Iranian initiation of theater and the phenomena of acting can be traced in the ancient epic ceremonial theaters such as <i>Sug-e SiÄvuÅ¡</i> ("mourning of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Siy%C3%A2vash" title="SiyÃ¢vash">SiÄvaÅ¡</a>"), as well as dances and theater narrations of Iranian mythological tales reported by <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Herodotus" title="Herodotus">Herodotus</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xenophon" title="Xenophon">Xenophon</a>.
